ial%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20on%20Tuesday's%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FOHcFGPewZTo%3Fsi%3D03x8tBB8QUKF0p50%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAspire%20with%20Emma%20Grede%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20the%20fashion%20designer%20said%20she%20refused%20to%20compromise%20on%20family%20time%2C%20even%20as%20her%20company%20demanded%20more%20of%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20one%20thing%20I%20would%20never%20trade%20off%20was%20being%20a%20good%20mom%2C%26quot%3B%20Burch%20told%20podcast%20host%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskims-cofounder-emma-grede-wfh-remote-work-downsides-social-issues-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEmma%20Grede%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20thought%20I%20could%20start%20a%20business%20if%20that%20were%20to%20have%20to%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurch%20shares%20three%20sons%20with%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20J.%20Christopher%20Burch%2C%20with%20whom%20she%20co-founded%20her%20namesake%20label%20in%202004.%20The%20pair%20divorced%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20got%20divorced%2C%20I%20was%20raising%20my%20kids%20a%20lot%20on%20my%20own.%20So%2C%20it%20was%20being%20at%20the%20doctor%2C%20going%20to%20a%20lacrosse%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20Burch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrawing%20from%20her%20own%20experience%2C%20Burch%20said%20she%20set%20out%20to%20build%20a%20flexible%20company%20culture%20that%20supports%20women%20balancing%20work%20and%20motherhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20done%20it%2C%20and%20what%20I%20say%20is%20that%20as%20long%20as%20it%20gets%20done%2C%20I'm%20not%20really%20clocking%20how%20it%20gets%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Burch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20made%20a%20point%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquiet-quitting-accounting-job-hapiness-work-culture-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleaving%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20soon%20as%20she%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20used%20to%20do%20that%2C%20maybe%20not%20at%20five%2C%20but%20I%20would%20be%20a%20stickler%20for%20being%20at%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%2C%20if%20anything%20suffered%2C%20it%20was%20my%20social%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20was%20%26quot%3Bfine%26quot%3B%20with%20her%2C%20since%20motherhood%20has%20been%20the%20most%20fulfilling%20part%20of%20her%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20I%20will%20say%2C%20being%20a%20mom%20is%20the%20joy%20of%20my%20life.%20And%20I%20often%20say%20I'm%20a%20survivor%20of%20raising%20three%20boys%2C%20because%20it's%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurch%20recalled%20how%20her%20sons%20were%20like%20little%20%26quot%3Btorturers%26quot%3B%20who%20used%20to%20%26quot%3Bbully%26quot%3B%20her%2C%20though%20she%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Btough%20mom.%26quot%3B%20Now%20in%20their%2020s%2C%20they%20sometimes%20apologize%20for%20what%20they%20put%20her%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20Burch%20said%20she%20didn't%20see%20it%20as%20making%20sacrifices%2C%20but%20as%20working%20around%20both%20her%20personal%20and%20professional%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20the%20only%20thing%20that%20was%20sacrificed%20is%20my%20sleep%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20still%20don't%20sleep%2C%20but%20I%20think%2C%20you%20know%2C%20for%20me%2C%20I%20would%2C%20you%20know%2C%20get%20the%20kids%20handled%20and%20put%20to%20bed%20and%20then%20start%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20simply%20part%20of%20the%20reality%20of%20running%20a%20company%2C%20Burch%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20will%20say%20I%20can%20turn%20it%20off%20very%20easily%2C%20too.%20I%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20outside%20passions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurch%20isn't%20the%20only%20high-profile%20figure%20to%20speak%20about%20the%20realities%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business