0converging%20into%20a%20C-shape.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20macro%20trends%20are%20boosting%20spending%20from%20lower-income%20consumers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20other%20company%20executives%20have%20said%20that%20the%20economy%20is%20more%20divided%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHilton's%20CEO%20said%20America's%20K-shaped%20economy%20is%20converging%20as%20lower-income%20consumers%20are%20spending%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20Tuesday%20earnings%20call%2C%20CEO%20Christopher%20Nassetta%20said%20that%20he%20expects%20%26quot%3Bimproving%20performance%20in%20the%20lower%20and%20mid-chain%20scales%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20sales%20growth%20would%20continue%20to%20%26quot%3Bmove%20downstream%20from%20luxury%20and%20upper%20upscale%20toward%20a%20more%20balanced%20convergence%20demand%20shape%2C%20or%20what%20I%20have%20been%20calling%20a%20C-shaped%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20is%20a%20play%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fk-shaped-economy-spending-jobs-income-credit-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EK-shaped%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Analysts%20and%20company%20executives%20have%20warned%20about%20the%20economy%20going%20K-shaped%20in%20recent%20months%20%E2%80%94%20a%20difference%20in%20spending%20behavior%20between%20high-%20and%20low-earners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20why%20he%20predicted%20a%20%26quot%3BC-shaped%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Nassetta%20said%20factors%20like%20falling%20inflation%2C%20the%20expectation%20of%20lowered%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20heavy%20investment%20in%20AI%20are%20%26quot%3Bbenefiting%20the%20middle%20and%20lower%20income%20consumer%20and%20driving%20broader%20demand%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20these%20were%20broad%2C%20big-picture%20trends%2C%20adding%20that%20people%20should%20%26quot%3Bforget%2C%20for%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20spike%20in%20energy%20prices%20and%20oil%