%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fkunchenguid%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKun%20Chen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20engineer%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Atlassian%2C%20said%20that%20he%20used%20a%20simple%20test%20to%20decide%20whether%20it%20was%20time%20to%20leave.%20Chen%2C%20said%20he%20decided%20to%20leave%20Microsoft%20when%20he%20realized%20he%20was%20no%20longer%20growing%20much%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%2C%20he%20said%2C%20wait%20until%20they%20miss%20a%20promotion%20to%20realize%20they're%20no%20longer%20growing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20very%20lagging%20indicator.%20I%20think%20actually%20we%20can%20tell%20if%20we're%20growing%20much%2C%20much%20earlier%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dq3ca41YIZjc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20since%20starting%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20he%20had%20been%20regularly%20asking%20himself%20a%20simple%20question%20to%20keep%20himself%20honest%20about%20his%20growth%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20I%20do%20this%20month%20that%20I%20couldn't%20last%20month%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20six%20years%20into%20his%20first%20job%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20realized%20he%20couldn't%20give%20himself%20a%20good%20answer%20to%20that%20question%20for%20a%20few%20months.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20podcast%2C%20he%20said%20that%20he%20was%20mainly%20working%20on%20the%20same%20tasks%2C%20and%20he%20already%20knew%20how%20to%20do%20them.%20He%20said%20that%20while%20he%20could%20find%20ways%20to%20do%20some%20of%20his%20work%20faster%20and%20better%2C%20it%20was%20still%20largely%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20I%20knew%20I%20wasn't%20growing%20as%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20said%20that%20a%20monthly%20test%20is%20especially%20relevant%20given%20the%20current%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fey-talent-chief-ai-changing-employee-recruitment-evaluations-promotions-careers-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epace%20of%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20engineering%20field%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20radical%20transformation%2C%20as%20AI%20models%20have%20improved%20dramatically%20over%20the%20past%20several%20months.%20Google%2C%20for%20example%2C%20just%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-generated-code-75-gemini-agents-software-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E75%25%20of%20its%20new%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20now%20generated%20by%20AI.%20Last%20fall%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it%20was%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20world%20is%20changing%20very%20fast%2C%20and%20we%20should%20constantly%20question%20ourselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20automatically%20mean%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbank-of-america-exec-shares-lessons-learned-from-missing-promotion-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkers%20should%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20company%20or%20team%20if%20they%20find%20themselves%20stagnant%20in%20their%20roles%2C%20Chen%20said%20on%20the%20podcast.%20Still%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20worth%20asking%20yourself%20the%20question%20so%20that%20you%20can%20figure%20out%20what%20kind%20of%20changes%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20could%20have%20spoken%20with%20his%20manager%20at%20Microsoft%20to%20discuss%20ways%20to%20move%20to%20a%20project%20or%20role%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20keep%20growing%20and%20learning%20new%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20he%20ultimately%20realized%20that%20switching%20to%20a%20smaller%20company%20with%20a%20very%20different%20culture%20and%20business%20model%20would%20give%20him%20a%20different%20level%20of%20growth.%20He%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20Facebook's%20stock%20was%20rising%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20he%20figured%20it%20was%20a%20good%20time%20to%20give%20it%20a%20try%2C%20and%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20best%20decisions%20he%20made%2C%20both%20financially%20and%20for%20his%20personal%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChen%20ended%20up%20coming%20back%20to%20Microsoft%20after%20his%20project%20at%20Facebook%20was%20%26quot%3Bwell-established%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bremaining%20work%20was%20more%20incremental.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20he%20had%20an%20opportunity%20at%20Microsoft%20to%20help%20bootstrap%20a%20new%20games%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20that%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20apply%20what%20I%20learned%20during%20my%20years%20at%20Facebook%2C%26quot%3B%20Chen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-microsoft-engineer-shares-test-to-decide-whether-to-quit-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777414161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f120223b4f7c3af2b7ad7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-microsoft-engineer-shares-test-to-decide-whether-to-quit-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kun%20Chen%2C%20an%20ex-Microsoft%20and%20Meta%20engineer%2C%20said%20that%20he%20asked%20himself%20a%20question%20to%20determine%20whether%20he%20was%20still%20growing%20in%20his%20role.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anthropic%20quietly%20