2%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236732572%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Quixote%20Studios%20is%20shuttering%20its%20Atlanta-based%20production%20services%20business%20and%20winding%20down%20its%20soundstage%20business%20in%20L.A.%20amid%20an%20ongoing%20production%20slump%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20Tuesday.%20The%20changes%20will%20mean%20layoffs%20for%20about%2070%20people%20in%20Atlanta%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%20Hudson%20Pacific%20Properties%20bought%20the%20company%20in%202022%20for%20%24360%20million%2C%20but%20has%20since%20had%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Gmaddaus%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Disney%20has%20decided%20to%20keep%20ESPN%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Disney%20CEO%20Josh%20D'Amaro%20at%20the%20annual%20Sun%20Valley%20conference%20in%20Idaho%2C%202025%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f1118929fef86fd43d3b6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDisney%20CEO%20Josh%20D'Amaro%20has%20decided%20to%20hang%20on%20to%20ESPN%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20first%20big%20calls%20of%20his%20tenure.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EESPN%20used%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20assets%20in%20media.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat's%20changed%2C%20because%20the%20media%20world%20has%20changed%2C%20and%20Disney%20has%20debated%20spinning%20out%20ESPN%20as%20a%20stand-alone%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-ceo-josh-damaro-background-parks-experiences-bob-iger-replacement-2026-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20CEO%20Josh%20D'Amaro%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20decided%20to%20keep%20ESPN%20in-house%2C%20for%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20has%20decided%20against%20spinning%20off%20ESPN%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20in%20one%20of%20the%20first%20major%20calls%20of%20new%20CEO%20Josh%20D'Amaro's%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20whether%20Disney%20would%20turn%20ESPN%20into%20a%20stand-alone%20company%20has%20hung%20over%20the%20company%20for%20years%2C%20as%20some%20investors%20and%20analysts%20argued%20that%20the%20declining%20cable%20business%20was%20a%20drag%20on%20the%20larger%20company's%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20sports%20network%20will%20stay%20inside%20the%20media%20giant%2C%20which%20thinks%20its%20presence%20will%20help%20its%20pivot%20to%20streaming%2C%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffcc-reviews-disney-abc-licenses-dei-policy-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDisney%20is%20facing%20a%20probe%20by%20the%20Federal%20Communications%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20its%20ABC%20broadcast%20licenses%2C%20a%20review%20that%20was%20announced%20a%20day%20after%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20called%20on%20the%20company%20to%20fire%20comedian%20Jimmy%20Kimmel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ED'Amaro%20could%20revisit%20his%20decision%20on%20ESPN%20in%20the%20future%2C%20people%20inside%20the%20company%20noted.%20But%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20it's%20a%20non-discussion%2C%20I'm%20told.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20Disney%20will%20continue%20with%20efforts%20to%20offer%20ESPN%20to%20customers%20in%20multiple%20ways%3A%20as%20part%20of%20its%20traditional%20cable%20bundle%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20streaming%20bundle%20with%20Hulu%20and%20Disney%2B%2C%20and%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fespn-streaming-jimmy-pitaro-sports-betting-diversity-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estreaming%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20And%20it%20may%20also%20look%20for%20other%20partners%20to%20take%20minority%20interests%20in%20the%20company%2C%20like%20it%20did%20when%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-nfl-deal-shows-who-owns-tv-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esold%20a%2010%25%20stake%20in%20the%20company%20to%20the%20NFL%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20executives%2C%20including%20former%20CEO%20Bob%20Iger%2C%20have%20repeatedly%20described%20ESPN%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcore%26quot%3B%20asset%2C%20but%20have%20also%20never%20fully%20closed%20the%20door%20to%20a%20sale.%20I've%20asked%20Disney%20for%20comment%3B%20an%20ESPN%20rep%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20Disney%20has%20previously%20discussed%20whether%20ESPN%20should%20remain%20inside%20the%20company%20shows%20you%20just%20how%20much%20the%20media%20landscape%20has%20changed%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20ESPN%20was%20a%20profit-making%20colossus%20that%20could%20charge%20cable%20distributors%20just%20about%20anything%20it%20wanted%2C%20and%20spent%20freely%20to%20lock%20up%20sports%20rights.%20But%20in%202015%2C%20Iger%20shocked%20the%20media%20industry%20by%20acknowledging%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2015%2F8%2F5%2F11615370%2Fcord-cutting-contagion-wall-street-bails-on-big-media-stocks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EESPN%20was%20losing%20subscribers%20because%20of%20cord-cutting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20since%20then%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20debate%20in%20and%20outside%20the%20company%20about%20the%20best%20way%20to%20use%20a%20big%20but%20declining%20asset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fespn-disney-spin-sell-decision-josh-damaro-2026-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777409482000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f116ad3b4f7c3af2b7ad0f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fespn-disney-spin-sell-decision-josh-damaro-2026-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Disney%20had%20previously%20considered%20spinning%20out%20the%20sports%20network.%20New%20CEO%20Josh%20D'Amaro%20has%20decided%20not%20to%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Music%20Industry%20Moves%3A%20Avex%20Secures%20%24100%20Million%20for%20Catalog%20Acquisitions%2C%20Harry%20Chapin%20Estate%20Partners%20With%20Primary%20Wave%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1777409220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236732678%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Avex%20Music%20Group%2C%20the%20global%20music%20company%20of%20Japanese%20entertainment%20giant%20Avex%20helmed%20by%20CEO%20Brandon%20Silverstein%2C%20has%20announced%20the%20launch%20of%20a%20%24100%20million%20fund%20to%20be%20aimed%20at%20catalog%20acquisitions%2C%20structured%20through%20a%20financing%20deal%20with%20City%20National%20Bank.%20According%20to%20the%20announcement%2C%20the%20deal%20was%20funded%20by%20%2450%20million%20in%20equity%20alongside%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Jem%20Aswad%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Best%20dog%20DNA%20tests%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20buy%20through%20our%20links%2C%20Business%20Insider%20may%20earn%20an%20affiliate%20commission.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELearn%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20dogs%20lie%20on%20a%20carpet%20beside%20several%20dog%20DNA%20test%20kits%20and%20packages%20arranged%20between%20them.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ef9b483fecbb42897a49c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20collected%20samples%20from%20our%20dogs%20using%20seven%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20dog%20DNA%20tests.%3Cp%3ERachael%20Schultz%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20your%20dog%20looks%20like%20a%20husky%2C%20recalls%20like%20a%20bird%20dog%2C%20or%20behaves%20like%20something%20entirely%20unknown%2C%20a%20DNA%20test%20can%20uncover%20fascinating%20insights%20about%20them.%20These%20tests%20can%20help%20decode%20their%20breed%20ancestry%2C%20identify%20potential%20genetic%20health%20risks%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20shed%20light%20on%20some%20of%20their%20wacky%20behavior%20traits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDog%20DNA%20tests%20analyze%20thousands%20of%20genetic%20markers%20from%20your%20dog's%20sample%20and%20compare%20them%20against%20an%20internal%20reference%20panel%20of%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dogs%20to%20identify%20the%20breeds%20that%20match%20most%20closely.%20These%20tests%20also%20screen%20your%20dog's%20DNA%20for%20markers%20tied%20to%20certain%20physical%20traits%2C%20like%20coat%20color%20or%20hairlessness%2C%20as%20well%20as%20mutations%20associated%20with%20increased%20risk%20for%20certain%20health%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20here's%20the%20catch%3A%20There's%20no%20universal%20canine%20DNA%20database%2C%20so%20each%20testing%20company%20relies%20on%20its%20own%20reference%20panel%20and%20breed%20database.%20And%20there's%20a%20lot%20that%20genetics%20can't%20fully%20explain%2C%20like%20personality%20and%20behavior.%20That%20means%20your%20dog's%20DNA%20reports%20are%20better%20viewed%20as%20informed%20estimates%20rather%20than%20definitive%20genetic%20blueprints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20guide%2C%20my%20editor%20and%20I%20tested%20seven%20leading%20dog%20DNA%20tests%20with%20three%20different%20dogs.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%